    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1922-11-14T11:40:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1922-11-14T11:40:00-05:00" n="79"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d79">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">839.6463/73: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in the Dominican Republic</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Russell</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Santo Domingo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-11-14T12:00:00-04:40">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 14, 1922—noon</hi>
                        </date>.<lb/>[Received November 15—6:30 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>42. Yesterday I had an interview with the Minister of Interior who has just
                    returned from Santiago and he informs me that the question of the Santo Domingo
                    Water, Light and Power Company will be settled satisfactorily in two or three
                    months. The municipality of Santiago has contracted with the General Electric
                    Company for an engineer to make a report on the line and plant and as soon as an
                    estimate is made of the amount necessary for putting plant in good condition
                    materials will be ordered and negotiations with the company closed.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Russell</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
